<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="fr">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Debian 13 "Trixie" – Guide Gaming (FR/EN)</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0f1115;
      --panel: #161a22;
      --accent: #54a8ff;
      --accent-2: #8be9fd;
      --text: #e6e6e6;
      --muted: #b9c0cf;
      --code-bg: #111622;
      --code-border: #243049;
      --green: #8df38b;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html, body { height: 100%; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji";
      background: radial-gradient(1200px 700px at 50% -10%, #14203a33, transparent), linear-gradient(180deg, #0c0e13, #0f1115);
      color: var(--text);
    }
    header {
      position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10;
      background: rgba(15,17,21,0.85);
      backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid #1e2430;
    }
    .container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 16px 18px; }
    h1 { margin: 12px 0; font-size: 28px; color: var(--accent); }
    h2 { color: var(--accent); margin: 30px 0 12px; border-bottom: 1px dashed #263247; padding-bottom: 6px; }
    h3 { color: var(--accent-2); margin: 18px 0 8px; }
    p, li { color: var(--muted); }
    .card {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid #22293a;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 18px;
      margin: 16px 0;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    }
    .note { border-left: 4px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 14px; }
    pre {
      position: relative;
      background: var(--code-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--code-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 10px 0 16px;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }
    code { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", monospace; font-size: 14px; }
    .copy {
      position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px;
      border: 1px solid #324261;
      background: #182034;
      color: #cfe3ff;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: 12px;
      padding: 6px 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    .copy:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
    footer { color: #9fb4d1; font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.85; padding: 24px 0 40px; }
    .small { font-size: 13px; color: #a9b6c8; }
    .ok { color: var(--green); font-weight: 600; }
    .kbd { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", monospace; background:#1a2133; border:1px solid #2a3857; padding:2px 6px; border-radius:6px;}
    .lang { font-size: 12px; color: #b3c4df; background:#1a2338; border:1px solid #2b3a5e; padding:2px 8px; border-radius: 999px; display:inline-block; }
    .center { text-align:center; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>🎮 Debian 13 "Trixie" – Guide Gaming (FR/EN)</h1>
      <div class="small">Toujours centré • Always centered • Maintained by <span class="kbd">mrthp</span></div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <div class="card note">
      <p><b>FR</b> — Les blocs identiques FR/EN sont fusionnés en un seul. Les différences sont précisées dans le texte. Toujours affiché en colonne unique, centré, même en ultra‑widescreen.<br>
      <b>EN</b> — Identical FR/EN blocks are merged. Differences are noted in text. Always single‑column, centered, even on ultra‑wide screens.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="repos">1) Dépôts / Repositories <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p class="center">Edit/Éditez <span class="kbd">/etc/apt/sources.list</span> and replace/et remplacez:</p>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list</code></pre>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>deb http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
deb-src http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie main contrib non-free non-free-firmware

deb http://deb.debian.org/debian-security trixie-security main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
deb-src http://deb.debian.org/debian-security trixie-security main contrib non-free non-free-firmware

deb http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie-updates main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
deb-src http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie-updates main contrib non-free non-free-firmware

# Backports
deb http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie-backports main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
deb-src http://deb.debian.org/debian trixie-backports main contrib non-free non-free-firmware</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="curl,wget">2) install curl et wget <span class="lang">FR</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install -y curl wget</code></pre>
    </div>



    <h2 id="liquorix">2) Noyau Liquorix / Liquorix Kernel <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>curl -s 'https://liquorix.net/install-liquorix.sh' | sudo bash</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="gpu">3) Pilotes GPU / GPU Drivers</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>NVIDIA (RTX 4000 series, 4060 etc.) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install -y extrepo
sudo extrepo enable nvidia-cuda
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y nvidia-driver nvidia-cuda-toolkit nvidia-settings</code></pre>
      <p class="small">Wayland works, but explicit sync/XWayland may be better for some titles. <span class="ok">DLSS/NVENC</span> require proprietary drivers (installed above).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>AMD (RX 7800 / RX 7900, RDNA3) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install -y firmware-amd-graphics mesa-vulkan-drivers mesa-vulkan-drivers:i386</code></pre>
      <ul>
        <li>FR — pilote <b>amdgpu</b> dans le noyau, Vulkan 64/32 bits, Wayland fluide.</li>
        <li>EN — <b>amdgpu</b> kernel driver, Vulkan 64/32‑bit, smooth Wayland.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 id="i386">4) Plateforme 32‑bit / 32‑bit Platform <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -t trixie-backports libgl1-mesa-dri:i386 libglx-mesa0:i386 mesa-vulkan-drivers:i386 libgbm1:i386 mesa-libgallium:i386
sudo apt install steam-installer</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="nvidiasmi">5) nvidia-smi (optionnel / optional) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>wget https://us.download.nvidia.com/XFree86/Linux-x86_64/580.65.06/NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-580.65.06.run -O NVIDIA.run
chmod +x NVIDIA.run
./NVIDIA.run --extract-only
sudo cp NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-580.65.06/nvidia-smi /usr/local/bin/
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/nvidia-smi
rm -rf NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-580.65.06 NVIDIA.run</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="utils">6) Utilitaires / Utilities</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Solaar (Logitech Unifying) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install solaar
sudo nano /etc/udev/rules.d/42-logitech-unify-permissions.rules
# Logitech Unifying Receiver / Bolt Receiver
KERNEL=="hidraw*", ATTRS{idVendor}=="046d", MODE="0660", GROUP="plugdev", TAG+="uaccess", TAG+="udev-acl"

sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
sudo udevadm trigger</code></pre>

      <h3>Brave Browser <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>curl -fsS https://dl.brave.com/install.sh | sh</code></pre>

      <h3>Docker + SearXNG <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>### Install Docker Searxng


Solution en deux étapes très simples
1️⃣ docker.sh –  installe Docker, active le service, ajoute l’utilisateur au groupe docker et redémarre la machine.

2️⃣ searxng.sh – à exécuter après le redémarrage (le groupe docker est alors actif) : il télécharge l’image SearXNG, crée le docker‑compose.yml, démarre le stack et ouvre automatiquement la page d’accueil dans le navigateur par défaut.
</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="build">7) Outils de build / Build Tools <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install build-essential -y</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="reboot">8) Redémarrage / Reboot <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo reboot</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="gaming">9) 🎮 Gaming Setup</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Steam <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install steam-installer -y</code></pre>

      <h3>Gamemode <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install gamemode -y</code></pre>

      <h3>Flatpak <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install flatpak plasma-discover-backend-flatpak -y     # KDE
sudo apt install flatpak gnome-software-plugin-flatpak -y    # GNOME
sudo flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo</code></pre>

      <h3>Exemples / Examples (Flatpak) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo flatpak install flathub com.vysp3r.ProtonPlus
sudo flatpak install flathub org.dupot.easyflatpak</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 id="protonplus-native">10) Installer ProtonPlus (native) / Install ProtonPlus (native) <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>Construit depuis les sources (GTK4 + libadwaita). Build from source.</p>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install -y git gettext meson valac desktop-file-utils libappstream-glib-dev libgee-0.8-dev libglib2.0-dev libgtk-4-dev libjson-glib-dev libadwaita-1-dev libarchive-dev libsoup-3.0-dev</code></pre>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>git clone https://github.com/Vysp3r/ProtonPlus.git && cd ProtonPlus
./scripts/build.sh native
cd build-native/
sudo ninja install</code></pre>
      <p class="small">Si <code>ninja</code> n'est pas présent : <code>sudo apt install ninja-build</code></p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="fastfetch">11) Installer Fastfetch et l'ajouter au .bashrc / Install Fastfetch and add to .bashrc <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo apt install -y fastfetch</code></pre>
      <p>Ajouter à la fin de <span class="kbd">~/.bashrc</span> (affiche Fastfetch pour les shells interactifs seulement) :</p>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>cat &gt;&gt; ~/.bashrc &lt;&lt;'EOF'
# Show fastfetch on interactive shells
case $- in
  *i*) if command -v fastfetch &gt;/dev/null 2&gt;&amp;1; then fastfetch; fi ;;
esac
EOF</code></pre>
      <p class="small">Recharge la configuration : <code>source ~/.bashrc</code></p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="tweaks">12) ⚙️ System Tweaks <span class="lang">FR/EN</span></h2>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Swappiness</h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>sudo sysctl vm.swappiness=10
echo 'vm.swappiness=10' | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/99-swappiness.conf > /dev/null</code></pre>

      <h3>OpenRGB Udev Rules</h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>curl -fsSL https://openrgb.org/releases/release_0.9/60-openrgb.rules -o /tmp/60-openrgb.rules
sudo install -m 0644 /tmp/60-openrgb.rules /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/60-openrgb.rules
sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
sudo udevadm trigger
flatpak install flathub org.openrgb.OpenRGB</code></pre>
    </div>

      <h3>Artemis The unified RGB platform</h3>
      <pre><button class="copy">Copy</button><code>curl -s -L https://artemis-rgb.com/binaries/install-artemis-rgb.sh | bash</code></pre>
    </div>


      <h3>ZRAM</h3>
      <pre><code>sudo apt install -y zram-tools
sudo nano /etc/default/zramswap
ALGO=zstd
PERCENT=50
sudo systemctl enable --now zramswap.service</code></pre>
    </div>

      <h3>OpenRGB en Appimage</h3>
      <pre><code>sudo apt install -y fuse libfuse2
wget https://openrgb.org/releases/release_candidate_1.0rc1/OpenRGB_1.0rc1_x86_64_1fbacde.AppImage
chmod +x OpenRGB_1.0rc1_x86_64_1fbacde.AppImage</code></pre>
    </div>


    <footer>
      <p>Hosted by <b>mrthp.ovh</b> — Fichier statique HTML. Placez à <span class="kbd">/debian13.html</span> ou utilisez une réécriture pour <span class="kbd">/debian13</span>.</p>
    </footer>
  </main>

  <script>
    // Copy buttons
    document.querySelectorAll('pre .copy').forEach(function(btn){
      btn.addEventListener('click', async function(){
        const code = this.nextElementSibling.innerText;
        try {
          await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code);
          const old = this.textContent;
          this.textContent = 'Copied ✓';
          this.style.borderColor = '#4caf50';
          this.style.color = '#bfffc1';
          setTimeout(() => { this.textContent = old; this.style.borderColor=''; this.style.color=''; }, 1300);
        } catch (e) {
          this.textContent = 'Copy failed';
          setTimeout(() => { this.textContent = 'Copy'; }, 1200);
        }
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
